Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Place @butter{3%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; bring to room temperature. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{2} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Peel @garlic{2%cloves}; place cloves in the center of a small piece of #foil{}. Cinch foil into a packet.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp}, @Fry Seasoning{1}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add garlic foil packet to same baking sheet. Roast on top rack until potatoes are tender and garlic is softened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, pat @Ranch Steak{1} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add shallot, @Green Beans{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until water has evaporated and green beans are tender, ~{6-7%minutes}. (If necessary, add another splash of water to help soften.) Stir in as many @Chili Flakes{1} as you'd like. Turn off heat.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Carefully remove garlic from foil; transfer to a cutting board and sprinkle with a pinch of salt. Mash cloves with a #fork{} until smooth, then add as much as you'd like to bowl with softened butter. (If butter is still cold, microwave for ~{5-10%seconds}.) Season with salt and pepper; stir to combine.

Divide sliced steak, roasted potatoes, and green beans between plates. Top steak with garlic butter. Serve potatoes with @mayonnaise{1} on the side for dipping.

> To make Magic Dipping Sauce, combine mayo with a squeeze of ketchup and mustard from your pantry!